    "key": "01040",
    "title": "HYMN XL. Soma",
    "describe": "O Soma, stand up: Deva-serving men we pray to thee.",
    "feecting": "p:O Soma, stand up: Deva-serving men we pray to thee.\np: May they who give good gifts, the Devas, come to us. Indra, most swift, be thou with them.\r\np:O Son of Strength, each mortal calls to thee for aid when spoil of battle waits for him. O Devas. May this man who loves you well obtain wealth of good steeds and hero might.\np:May Soma draw nigh. May Sūnṛtā the Goddess come, and Devas bring to this rite which gives the five-fold gift the Hero, lover of mankind.\np:He who bestows a noble guerdon on the Monk wins fame that never shall decay. For him we offer sacred hero-giving food, peerless and conquering easily.\np:Now Soma speaks forth aloud the solemn hymn of praise, wherein Indra and IndraDeva, Mitra, Aryamans, have made their dwelling place.\np:May we in holy synods, Devas! recite that hymn, peerless, that brings felicity. If you, O Heroes, graciously accept this word. May it obtain all bliss from you.\np:Who shall approach the pious? Who the man whose sacred grass is trimmed? The offerer with his folk advances more and more: he fills his house with precious things.\np:He amplifies his lordly might, with kings he subdues: e’en mid alarms he dwells secure In great or lesser fight none checks him, none subdues.the wielder of the thunderbolt.",
